			<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="index.html?p=50" title="Permalink to Vermont apartment fires and inspection​s examined by VPR this week" rel="bookmark">Vermont apartment fires and inspection​s examined by VPR this week</a></h2>

			<div class="entry-meta">
				<p class="slug">Posted August 13, 2013 <!--by admin--></p>			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->

				<div class="entry-content">
				<p>Preventing the devastating effects of apartment fires on Vermont renters is the subject of  a week-long series on Vermont Public Radio this week.</p>
<div><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="font-family: Calibri;"><span style="color: #000000;">The series, </span><em><a href="http://digital.vpr.net/topic/burned-out-vermonts-apartment-fires" target="_blank"><span style="color: #0c4ca2;">Burned Out: Vermont&#8217;s Apartment Fires</span></a></em><span style="color: #000000;">, includes an interview with Vermont Rental Codes website co-creator Jessica Radbord, a lawyer with Vermont Legal Aid. </span></span></span></div>
<div></div>
							</div><!-- .entry-content -->
	
			<div class="entry-utility">
									<p class="postFooter"><span class="cat-links">
						Posted in <a href="index.html?cat=1" rel="category">Uncategorized</a>					</span>
					<!--<span class="meta-sep">|</span>-->
												<!--<span class="comments-link"><a href="http://www.rentalcodes.org/news/?p=50#respond" title="Comment on Vermont apartment fires and inspection​s examined by VPR this week">Leave a comment</a></span>-->
				</p>
			</div><!-- .entry-utility -->
		</div><!-- #post-## -->

		
	


			<div id="post-47" class="post-47 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized">
			<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="index.html?p=47" title="Permalink to Vermont Architects weigh in on vertical access requirement" rel="bookmark">Vermont Architects weigh in on vertical access requirement</a></h2>

			<div class="entry-meta">
				<p class="slug">Posted August 8, 2013 <!--by admin--></p>			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->

				<div class="entry-content">
				<p>The American Institute of Architects (AIA) Vermont Chapter is urging the Vermont Department of Public Safety to reconsider a requirement for vertical access in public spaces.</p>
<p>According to Tom Bachman, the chapter’s president, the requirement in spaces as little as 1,000 square feet is far stricter than the national level requirement and will likely reap unintended, negative consequences for Vermont.<br />
Read the <a href="http://www.vhfa.org/documents/housing_matters/2013/aia_letter_may2013.pdf">AIA May 2013 letter</a>.</p>
							</div><!-- .entry-content -->
	
			<div class="entry-utility">
									<p class="postFooter"><span class="cat-links">
						Posted in <a href="index.html?cat=1" rel="category">Uncategorized</a>					</span>
					<!--<span class="meta-sep">|</span>-->
												<!--<span class="comments-link"><a href="http://www.rentalcodes.org/news/?p=47#respond" title="Comment on Vermont Architects weigh in on vertical access requirement">Leave a comment</a></span>-->
				</p>
			</div><!-- .entry-utility -->
		</div><!-- #post-## -->

		
	


			<div id="post-42" class="post-42 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized">
			<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="index.html?p=42" title="Permalink to Vermont landlord certificates due to tenants" rel="bookmark">Vermont landlord certificates due to tenants</a></h2>

			<div class="entry-meta">
				<p class="slug">Posted April 4, 2013 <!--by admin--></p>			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->

				<div class="entry-content">
				<p><a href="http://www.vhfa.org/about/news/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Tax_Dept2.jpg"><img class="alignnone  wp-image-9107" style="border: 0pt none; float: right; padding-left: 10px; padding-bottom: 10px;" title="Tax_Dept" src="http://www.vhfa.org/about/news/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Tax_Dept2.jpg" alt="" width="350" height="211" /></a>Every year landlords are required to provide each of their tenants with a completed Landlord Certificate (LC-142) by January 31 if they have 2 or more residential units or upon request if they have only 1 residential unit, according to recent guidance from the VT Department of Taxes.</p>
<p>Read the March 15, 2013 <a href="http://www.vhfa.org/documents/housing_matters/2013/landlord_certificate_letter.pdf">letter from the VT Dept. of Taxes </a>or download the <a href="http://www.vhfa.org/redirect.php?url=www.state.vt.us/tax/pdf.word.excel/individual/2012LC-142-web.pdf">landlord certificate</a>.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
							</div><!-- .entry-content -->
	
