			<div id="post-34" class="post-34 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized">
			<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="index.html?p=34" title="Permalink to Updates to Vermont Plumbing Rules proposed" rel="bookmark">Updates to Vermont Plumbing Rules proposed</a></h2>

			<div class="entry-meta">
				<p class="slug">Posted April 2, 2013 <!--by admin--></p>			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->

				<div class="entry-content">
				<p><a href="http://www.vhfa.org/about/news/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/plumbing.jpg"><img title="plumbing" class="alignnone  wp-image-9063" style="border: 0pt none; float: right; padding-left: 10px; padding-bottom: 10px;" src="http://www.vhfa.org/about/news/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/plumbing.jpg" alt="" width="371" height="250" /></a></p>
<p>The <a href="http://firesafety.vermont.gov/professions/plumbing"><strong>Vermont Department of Public Safety</strong> </a>has proposed a series of updates to the Vermont Plumbing rules.</p>
<p>The anticipated deadline for public comment is May 21, 2013.  Comments may be submitted directly to Robert Patterson (<a href="mailto:robert.patterson@state.vt.us">robert.patterson@state.vt.us</a>).</p>
<p>Read the proposed rules with <a href="http://www.vhfa.org/documents/housing_matters/2013/2012_plumbing_rules_annotated.pdf">changes annotated</a> or   <a href="http://www.vhfa.org/documents/housing_matters/2013/2012_plumbing_rules.pdf">without annotations</a>.</p>
							</div><!-- .entry-content -->
	
			<div class="entry-utility">
									<p class="postFooter"><span class="cat-links">
						Posted in <a href="index.html?cat=1" rel="category">Uncategorized</a>					</span>
